"c-234489" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Wendy <div class="commentdate">April  8, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>I have quite a bit of roasted thin asparagus spears left from Easter dinner.  I think I will make a cousin of this salad using that! Yum!!  Thanks for the inspiration.</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234492" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead"><a title="http://ofstrangersensibilities.blogspot.com" href="http://ofstrangersensibilities.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow">joy</a> <div class="commentdate">April  8, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>I've never had broccolinis before! looks delish.</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234493" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Alison <div class="commentdate">April  8, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>Made this on Saturday and got a big thumbs up from my husband.  Had to google scallions though - we call them spring onions here downunder!</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234498" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead"><a title="http://www.herriottgrace.com" href="http://www.herriottgrace.com" rel="nofollow">Nikole</a> <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>There's a special place in my heart for that first photo, Heidi. So nice.</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234502" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Eileen <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>I get tired of eating red pepper flakes and garlic with greens,  so i too can appreciate your yawn.  The salad looks great and I will give it a try with  buratta.  Anything with buratta is fantastic in my book!  I am mostly posting to tell you how much I am enjoying a recipe you posted a few years ago for walnut pesto with marjoram and parsley over farro pasta.  I wanted to make a quick vegetarian birthday meal and I made this pasta along with your tomato curry soup (forgot the recipe name).  They were not the best compliments for each other but we enjoyed both dishes very much.  I have made the pasta and walnut pesto three times since finding the recipe less than a month ago.  It has a very evocative taste.  Reminds me of Provance.  Thank You!</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234504" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead"><a title="http://www.weekenddoings.blogspot.com" href="http://www.weekenddoings.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow">Martha @ Weekend Doings</a> <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>It looks delicious! I love the idea of adding a hard boiled egg. Thank you for sharing this recipe.</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234505" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead"><a title="http://www.snappygourmet.com" href="http://www.snappygourmet.com" rel="nofollow">Lisa @ Snappy Gourmet</a> <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>Sounds delicious!</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234508" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">philbilly <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>looks like something the neighbors dog barfed up get some meat and taters maybe some corn too.</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /><div id="c-234509" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead"><a title="http://theshadypine.blogspot.com.au/" href="http://theshadypine.blogspot.com.au/" rel="nofollow">Anna @ the shady pine</a> <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2012</div></div><div class="commentbox"><p>I am loving just tender broccoli I in warm Autumn salads here in Australia at he moment.  So this is yet more lovely inspiration for this delicious ingredient!</p></div></div><div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br class="clear" /></div>


